    c.
        The total resistance of the loudspeakers in diagram three is higher, since they are in series. This can also be seen by the fact that V = IR, and V is constant, but I (current) is lower, so R must be higher. Namely, respectively, resistance must be 5 and 1.25 ohms. This can also be seen by the fact that the speakers in diagram 3 are in series but in parallel in diagram 4: resistance decreases if two components are connected in parallel but increases if they connect in series.
